link:labelLink.link:label: Contact Address Line 1
Contact Address Line 1 - First line utilising free format, that is used to create a semi structured address.
Contact Address Line 2
Contact Address Line 2 - Second line utilising free format, that is used to create a semi structured address.
Contact Address Line 3
Contact Address Line 3 - Third line utilising free format, that is used to create a semi structured address.
Contact email
Contact Fax Number - Area Code
Contact Fax Number - Area Code - This element describes a standard Australian Area Code as used in conjunction with facsimile numbers.
Contact Fax Number - Number
Contact Fax Number - Number - The number that is associated to a unique provision of telephone service connected to a facsimile machine for the contact person.
Contact Telephone - Area Code
Contact Telephone - Area Code - The standard Australian Area Code as used in conjunction with telephone numbers.
Contact Telephone - Number
Contact Telephone - Number - The number that is associated to a unique provision of telephone service for the contact person.
Request Cancellation Date
Request Cancellation Date - This is requested at the commencement of the annual reconciliation to set the liable to date for the reporting party.
Organisation Name Type
Organisation Name Type - MN - Main or legal name, MTR - Main trading name, OTR - Other trading name, OTH - Other name, MAU - Management accounting unit, UNK - Unknown
Reporting Party Name / Taxpayer Name
Group Member Name
Designated Group Employer Name
Expected Designated Group Employer Name
Single Lodger Member Name
Reporting Party Name / Taxpayer Name - Non editable, displayed for reporting party information only.

Group Member Name - A Designated Group Employer that wants to claim the deduction entitlement must declare in their lodgement all group members individually and disclose each group member's South Australian and interstate wages.
Designated Group Employer Name - Only requested when the reporting party is a group member (Group status GE). Required for each group status period.
Expected Designated Group Employer Name - This is required when the reporting party is a group member and is not the DGE
Single Lodger Member Name - The full name by which a Single Lodger Member reporting party is known. (Legal entity name)
Contact Name

Contact Name - The name of a person represented in a free format text. It may contain a complete name (first, family and other given names) or parts of it. This representation of a person's name is commonly used where the name is not used for proof of identity matching hence it is not required to be strongly validated. Examples of its use are: The name of the person who is used as a contact on behalf of an Organisation or the name of the recipient of a correspondence.
Annual Reconciliation ID
Annual Reconciliation ID - An identifier generated by the agency for successful lodgements. This is required for pre-fill of previously lodged forms.
Group Member Start Date
Single Lodger Member Start Date
Group Member Start Date - Start Date the group member was part of the DGE's group for the given status code and period. Dates must be within liable period
Single Lodger Member Start Date - Start Date the single lodger member was part of the NSL's group for the given status code and period. Dates must be within liable period
Group Member End Date
Single Lodger Member End Date
Group Member End Date - End Date the group member was part of the DGE's group for the given status code and period. Dates must be within liable period
Single Lodger Member End Date - End Date the single lodger member was part of the NSL's group for the given status code and period. Dates must be within liable period
Return Identifier
Return Identifier - A unique number generated by the agency to identify each return for a reporting party and period. This is required for pre-fill of forms.
Declaration Statement Accepted Indicator
Declaration Statement Accepted Indicator - Indicates that the terms stated in the Declaration have been accepted or declined by the Legal Obligation Party lodging the report.
Declaration Statement
Declaration Statement - The text that contains the terms and responsibilities of the statement made by the Legal Obligation Party when lodging a report.
Group Status Code
Expected Status Code

Group Status Code - Code used to specify the reporting party's group status: NGE - Non Grouped Employer DGE - Designated Group Employer GE - Grouped Employer NSL - Nominated Single Lodger SLM - Single Lodger Member NONNNSL - Non Nominated Single Lodger
Each status code must contain Period Start Date and Period End Date.
Expected Status Code - Group Status Code the reporting party expects to have in the following financial year
Commissions
Group Total Commissions
Commissions - Commissions deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Commissions - Commissions deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Fringe Benefits
Group Total Fringe Benefits
Fringe Benefits - Fringe Benefits deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Fringe Benefits - Fringe Benefits deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Calculated Tax Payable

Calculated Tax Payable - The calculated payroll tax amount is the calculated taxable amount multiplied by the applicable tax rate. The Calculated Payroll Tax is an estimate based on the information provided, a Commissioner's Assessment may be issued once data is reviewed by RevenueSA. This is not the figure that the entity is liable to pay as the existence of interest and penalty previously applied or assessed will affect the final assessment amount payable.
SA Wage Components Total
SA Taxable wages
SA Taxable Wages Total
Group Member Total SA Wages
Expected Employer SA Wages
Single Lodger Member Status Period Total SA Wages

SA Wage Components Total - SA taxable wages. SA wage components refers to the types of remunerations that are liable to payroll tax. SA wage components include:
Salaries and wages Fringe benefits Employer superannuation contributions Director's fees Payments to contractors under relevant contracts Allowances Share scheme contributions Bonuses and Allowances Commissions Employment termination payments
SA Taxable wages - SA Wages paid in South Australia in the given Group Status period.
SA Taxable Wages Total - Total of SA Wages paid in South Australia for all Group Status Periods for the entire liable period.
Group Member Total SA Wages - SA Wages paid in South Australia by the group member while a member of the DGE group
Expected Employer SA Wages - Estimated South Australian Taxable wages for the reporting party for the next financial year.
Single Lodger Member Status Period Total SA Wages - SA Wages paid in South Australia by the single lodger group member in the group status period
Interstate Wages
Group Member Total Interstate Wages
Expected Employer Interstate Wages
Single Lodger Member Status Period Total Interstate Wages

Interstate Wages - Total interstate wages paid in the given Group Status period. Interstate wages are wages that are taxable in other Australian States or Territories under laws that corresponds with home state Payroll Tax Act.
Group Member Total Interstate Wages - Interstate Wages paid by the group member while a member of the DGE group
Expected Employer Interstate Wages - Estimated Interstate taxable wages for the reporting party for the next financial year.
Single Lodger Member Status Period Total Interstate Wages - Interstate Wages paid by the single lodger group member in the group status period
Group SA Wages

Group SA Wages - As the Designated Group Employer for the selected Group Status period, you are required to declare all members of the group that paid wages in Australia during this period, and record their respective wages. If group member details are not declared the Designated Group Employer cannot claim the deduction entitlement.
Group Interstate wages

Group Interstate wages - As the Designated Group Employer for the group, you are required to declare all members of the group that paid wages in Australia during this period, and record their respective interstate wages.
Deduction Entitlement
Expected Annual Deduction

Deduction Entitlement - For South Australian payroll tax purposes the maximum deduction entitlement is determined by two factors. 1. The number of days that the organisation/group employed Australia wide during the financial year. 2. The portion of taxable wages (or group's taxable wages if applicable) that were paid in South Australia compared to their total Australia wide wages (or group's taxable Australia wide wages if applicable).
Expected Annual Deduction - Estimated annual deduction based on Expected Group Status Code, and expected South Australian and Interstate wages of the reporting party and Group Members
Taxable Amount

Taxable Amount - The taxable amount is the value on which payroll tax is calculated. To obtain this value, the Payroll Tax Deduction total amount is subtracted from the taxable wages for reporting party.
Reporting Party Number / Taxpayer Number
Group Member Reporting Party Number
Designated Group Employer Reporting Party number
Expected Designated Group Employer Number
Single Lodger Member Reporting Party Number
Reporting Party Number / Taxpayer Number - Non editable, displayed for reporting party information only.
Group Member Reporting Party Number - The reporting party identifier for the group member - South Australian taxpayer number
Designated Group Employer Reporting Party number - Only requested when the reporting party is a group member.
Expected Designated Group Employer Number - This is displayed when the reporting party is a group member and is not the DGE
Single Lodger Member Reporting Party Number - The reporting party identifier for the single lodger member - South Australian taxpayer number
Reason For Change

Reason For Change - 01 - Change in ownership 02 -Commenced or ceased to employ Interstate 03 - Change in control/decision making 04 - Acquired a controlling interest in another company 05 - Change to the Designated Group Employer 06 - Other
Change Status Comments
Change Status Comments - Free field - mandatory if there has been a change in status
Expected Other Group Member Interstate Wages

Expected Other Group Member Interstate Wages - An estimate of the total Interstate Taxable Wages of the other group members for this reporting party (I.e. DGE) will be paying in the following financial year
Expected Other Group Member SA Wages

Expected Other Group Member SA Wages - An estimate of the total South Australian Taxable Wages the other group members for this reporting party (I.e. DGE) will be paying in the following financial year
Interest Previously Applied
Interest Previously Applied - Total amount of interest applied to monthly defaults during the liable period and not remitted.
Penalty Previously Applied
Penalty Previously Applied - Total amount of penalty applied to monthly defaults during the liable period and not remitted.
Reporting Party Declared Total Amount Paid

Reporting Party Declared Total Amount Paid - User can override the RevenueSA Declared Total Amount Paid to calculate the total Balance Payable based on the revised figure. In this instance a note detailing individual payments or discrepancies during the liable period is mandatory.
Interest Applied to this Assessment
Interest Applied to this Assessment - Total amount of interest applied to this assessment. Applied in accordance with the Taxation Administration Act 1996
Penalty Applied to this Assessment
Penalty Applied to this Assessment - Total amount of penalty applied to this assessment. Applied in accordance with the Taxation Administration Act 1996
Direct Debit Authorisation Indicator
Direct Debit Authorisation Indicator - Used to indicate if the user authorises a direct debit payment
Salaries/Wages
Group Total Salaries/Wages
Salaries/Wages - Salaries/Wages deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Salaries/Wages - Salaries/Wages deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Bonuses / Allowances
Group Total Bonuses and Allowances
Bonuses / Allowances - Bonuses and allowances deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Bonuses and Allowances - Bonuses deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Directors Fees
Group Total Directors Fees
Directors Fees - Directors fees deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Directors Fees - Directors fees deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Termination Payments
Group Total Termination Payments
Termination Payments - Employee Termination payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009
Group Total Termination Payments - Employee Termination payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009
Shares and Options
Group Total Shares and Options
Shares and Options - Shares or options issued under employee share acquisition schemes deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Shares and Options - Shares or options issued under employee share acquisition schemes deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Other payments
Group Total Other Payments
Other payments - Any other types of payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009
Group Total Other Payments - Any other types of payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009
Other Payments Description
Group Total Other Payments Description
Other Payments Description - Explanation of the types of Other Payments recorded in SA0091
Group Total Other Payments Description - Explanation of the type(s) of Other Payments recorded in SA0091
Amount Paid Notes
Amount Paid Notes - Notes provided if the reporting party Declared Total Amount Paid is different to the RevenueSA Declared Total Amount Paid
Authorised Amount Payable
Authorised Amount Payable - The amount of tax the lodger elects to pay.
Contractor Payments
Group Total Contractor Payments
Contractor Payments - Contractor payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009. Refer to http://www.revenuesa.sa.gov.au/info_circulars/IC_005.pdf
Group Total Contractor Payments - Contractor payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009. Refer to http://www.revenuesa.sa.gov.au/info_circulars/IC_005.pdf
Recording Group Member Detail Indicator

Recording Group Member Detail Indicator - DGEs can elect not to provide any group members wages and not claim a deduction entitlement in South Australia. If this is not selected then no group member information is required
Request Cancellation Indicator
Request Cancellation Indicator - Indicator used by the reporting party to declare their intention to cancel their payroll tax registration
Amount Now Due
Refund Due

Amount Now Due - Amount Now Due is based on information entered relating to Calculated Tax Payable + Interest Previously Applied+ Penalty Previously Applied + Penalty Applied on Current Assessment + Interest Applied on the Current Assessment less reporting party Declared Amount Paid.

Refund Due - Amount of Refund Due based on information entered relating entered relating to Calculated Tax Payable + Interest Previously Applied+ Penalty Previously Applied + Penalty Applied on Current Assessment + Interest Applied on the Current Assessment less reporting party Declared Amount Paid
Employer Superannuation Payments
Group Total Employer Superannuation Payments
Employer Superannuation Payments - Employer Superannuation payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Group Total Employer Superannuation Payments - Employer Superannuation payments deemed taxable in South Australia under the Payroll Tax Act 2009.
Consent to Electronic Assessment
Consent to Electronic Assessment - Used to indicate whether an electronic or paper-based assessment is issued.
